    <div class="wrap">
      <h1>Age Suitability</h1>
      <p>PumpSync handles personal health-data portability for authorized Tandem Source and Apple Health users. It is not a game, social network, chat app, or medical advice product.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="wrap content">
        <article class="content-block">
          <h2>What PumpSync does</h2>
          <p>PumpSync syncs Tandem Source pump data to Apple Health at the user's request. It is intended for personal data portability and recordkeeping by users who are authorized to access the connected Tandem Source account and Apple Health data.</p>
        </article>

        <article class="content-block">
          <h2>What PumpSync does not do</h2>
          <ul>
            <li>PumpSync does not provide medical advice, diagnosis, treatment, or dosing recommendations.</li>
            <li>PumpSync does not include chat, messaging, social feeds, advertising, gambling, contests, loot boxes, or monetized chance mechanics.</li>
            <li>PumpSync does not provide unrestricted web access.</li>
            <li>PumpSync does not sell or share HealthKit data with advertisers, data brokers, or marketing services.</li>
          </ul>
        </article>

        <article class="content-block">
          <h2>Guidance for parents and guardians</h2>
          <p>Parents and guardians should supervise use by minors and confirm that the user is authorized to access the Tandem Source account, Apple Health data, PumpSync Hosted subscription, or self-hosted backend being used.</p>
          <p>Users should verify health data and follow guidance from qualified healthcare professionals before making health or treatment decisions.</p>
        </article>

        <article class="content-block">
          <h2>App Review context</h2>
          <p>Because PumpSync handles health-related records and writes to Apple Health only with permission, its age rating and review context may reflect health-data handling, third-party account access, and medical-disclaimer requirements rather than entertainment content.</p>
        </article>
    </div>
  </section>
</main>
